The paper uses proof techniques in coding theory and Fourier analysis to derive new bounds for non-interactive simulation of random variables, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper establishes new properties of the average distance and distance enumerator of binary block codes, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also uses hypercontractivity bounds, which could suggest that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
